Pessimism in the manufacturing deepened in the first quarter, the latest survey of sentiment in the sector shows.According to the University of Stellenbosch&rsquo;s Bureau for Economic Research (BER), manufacturing business confidence declined to 28 points in the quarter, from 30 points in the fourth quarter of 2016.At the current level, more than seven out of 10 manufacturers are unsatisfied with prevailing business conditions.Business confidence for the sector has been below the 50-point threshold between optimism and pessimism since the first half of 2011.The BER&rsquo;s survey of manufacturing companies is released ahead of manufacturing production results for the first quarter.Two weeks ago Statistics SA said manufacturing production was up 0.8% in January compared with the year-earlier period, lower than the Bloomberg consensus forecast of 1.6%.